# Design system enforcement

## Design token contract

- Use design-system exports from `#lib/design-system` for:
  - geometry
  - radius
  - typography
  - tracking
  - semantic variants
- Do not introduce raw geometry utilities such as:
  - `rounded-3xl`
  - `rounded-4xl`
  - `shadow-2xl`
  - arbitrary `rounded-[...]`
  - arbitrary shadow systems
- Exceptions must be explicitly allowlisted in:
  - `scripts/check-design-contract.mjs`

## Semantic color contract

- Semantic colors are defined centrally in:
  - `app/globals.css`
- Components must consume semantic tokens:
  - `bg-primary`
  - `text-muted-foreground`
  - `border-border`
  - etc.
- Avoid hardcoded color values in components unless explicitly approved.

## Primitive ownership contract

- UI primitives are owned by:
  - `components/ui/**`
- Application/features must import primitives only from:
  - `#components/ui/*`

Forbidden outside primitive layer:

```txt
@radix-ui/*
radix-ui
@base-ui/react
```

## Runtime validation contract

When variants, sizes, themes, or appearance values originate from:

- JSON
- CMS
- query params
- APIs
- external payloads

validate them using exported schemas from:

```txt
#lib/design-system
```

Examples:

```ts
buttonVariantSchema.parse(value)
buttonSizeSchema.parse(value)
```

## Anti-drift rules

- Prefer existing design-system patterns over introducing new visual abstractions.
- Do not create parallel token systems.
- Do not introduce local shadow/radius scales.
- Keep visual language structurally consistent across ERP modules.

## CI

Before merge, keep all checks green:

```bash
pnpm lint
pnpm typecheck
```

`pnpm lint` must include:

- ESLint
- `scripts/check-design-contract.mjs`
